---
import placeholderImage from '../../../public/assets/5.webp';
import SideNavigation from './SideNavigation.astro';
---

  <main class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <div class="lg:flex lg:gap-10">
      <aside class="lg:w-64 flex-shrink-0">
        <SideNavigation />
      </aside>
      <article class="mt-10 lg:mt-0 lg:flex-grow">
        <h1 class="text-6xl font-extrabold mb-8 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Sanarte Case Study</h1>
        
        <section id="project-overview" class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Client Background</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 ">my client is a researcher at a university in Canada, and he wants to use this project in both research purpose and as a source of income.<br/>
            he has that idea that we can improve remote workspaces using sounds, and different techniques.<br/>
            
            Also have good connections in the research market, so he wants to use that to generate more income.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="research-methods" class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Client Requirements</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 ">To design a mobile app that uses sound, to destress and increase the work quality and productivity or remote workers, to be used for research purpose, and to have the data sold later to research centers and universities. while also having the potential of growing in the future and being subscription based project (it has to be a mobile app not a slack or browser plugin)
            the data will be collected with the knowledge of the users, and wont be used except if the users accepts that again later on an email, and wont be linked to their personal data by anyway (for privacy consideration)           
            also, he wants business help to verify the idea, and if the users will really use the app</p>
        </section>

        <section id="research-methods" class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Problem statement</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 ">I am a leader in my company and I want to fix remote worker disconnection and I'm trying to Align my team so they are in better sync, happier and more productive - loving their job and their colleagues, but Remote workers are challenged to connect and openly share/engage to build true team synchronicity, because The recent challenges of the remote workplace have only worsened social isolation and loneliness. It reduces creativity, erodes performance, and increases turnover intention.</p>
        </section>



        <section id="research-methods" class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Business Goals</h2>
          <ul class="text-gray-600  list-disc">
            <li>to have enough users for testing AI models and then Selling them, and selling some analytics to research centers, and universities</li>
            <li>to keep the users for long enough and keep them engaged</li>
            <li>to be able to make deals with large remote teams.</li>

          </ul>
        </section>

        <section id="research-methods" class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Project goals</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 ">To Craft an Intuitive UI that Seamlessly Addresses User Needs, Resolves Pain Points, and Elevates the User Experience. Our Mission is to Create a Delightful Journey that Captivates Users and Inspires Lasting Engagement.</p>
        </section>

        <section id="research-methods" class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Hypotheses</h2>
          <ul class="text-gray-600  list-disc">
            <li>Remote workers often feel disconnected at their workplaces.</li>
            <li>Listening to music or sounds can help alleviate stress in remote workplaces.</li>
            <li>Listening to music increases worker productivity and work quality.</li>
            <li>Users are willing to use an app to listen to sounds that may seem strange (not music), but are proven to reduce stress and enhance productivity.</li>
            <li>my target audience are youth from the age of 25 - 40 who work remotely, and are tech savvy</li>

          </ul>
        </section>


        <section id="user-interviews" class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">User Interviews</h2>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-700 dark:divide-gray-800">
              <thead class="bg-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-800">
                <tr>
                  <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-primary-200/70 dark:text-primary-200/70 uppercase tracking-wider ">Participant</th>
                  <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-primary-200/70 dark:text-primary-200/70 uppercase tracking-wider ">Age</th>
                  <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-primary-200/70 dark:text-primary-200/70 uppercase tracking-wider ">Occupation</th>
                  <th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-xs font-medium text-primary-200/70 dark:text-primary-200/70 uppercase tracking-wider ">Key Pain Points</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="bg-gray-900 divide-y divide-gray-900 dark:bg-gray-900 dark:divide-gray-700">
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm text-primary-200 dark:text-primary-200">P1</td>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm text-primary-200 dark:text-primary-200">28</td>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm text-primary-200 dark:text-primary-200">Marketing Manager</td>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-primary-200 dark:text-primary-200 ">Difficulty in navigation, slow load times</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm text-primary-200 dark:text-primary-200">P1</td>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm text-primary-200 dark:text-primary-200">28</td>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm text-primary-200 dark:text-primary-200">Marketing Manager</td>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-primary-200 dark:text-primary-200 ">Difficulty in navigation, slow load times</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm text-primary-200 dark:text-primary-200">P1</td>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm text-primary-200 dark:text-primary-200">28</td>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 whitespace-nowrap text-sm text-primary-200 dark:text-primary-200">Marketing Manager</td>
                  <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-primary-200 dark:text-primary-200 ">Difficulty in navigation, slow load times</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="user-persona" class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">User Persona</h2>
          <img src={placeholderImage} alt="User Persona" width={800} height={400} class="rounded-lg shadow-md" />
        </section>

        <section id="user-journey-map" class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">User Journey Map</h2>
          <img src={placeholderImage} alt="User Journey Map" width={800} height={400} class="rounded-lg shadow-md" />
        </section>

        <section id="overall-analytics" class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Overall Analytics</h2>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
            <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 overflow-hidden shadow rounded-lg">
              <div class="px-4 py-5 sm:p-6">
                <dt class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-500  truncate">Bounce Rate</dt>
                <dd class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">45%</dd>
                <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 ">Down from 60% last quarter</dd>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 overflow-hidden shadow rounded-lg">
              <div class="px-4 py-5 sm:p-6">
                <dt class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-500  truncate">Avg. Session Duration</dt>
                <dd class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">3m 45s</dd>
                <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 ">Up 20% from previous version</dd>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 overflow-hidden shadow rounded-lg">
              <div class="px-4 py-5 sm:p-6">
                <dt class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-500  truncate">Conversion Rate</dt>
                <dd class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">2.5%</dd>
                <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 ">Improved by 0.8% after redesign</dd>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 overflow-hidden shadow rounded-lg">
              <div class="px-4 py-5 sm:p-6">
                <dt class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-500  truncate">User Satisfaction</dt>
                <dd class="mt-1 text-3xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">4.2/5</dd>
                <dd class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 ">Based on post-interaction surveys</dd>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section id="conclusion" class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Conclusion</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-600 ">The UX research revealed several key areas for improvement in our product. By addressing the identified pain points and implementing data-driven design decisions, we were able to significantly enhance user satisfaction and engagement metrics.</p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>
